## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

### DO NOT:
- Skip sections because they seem "less important"
- Summarize when you should extract verbatim
- Ignore appendices or supplementary materials
- Create MDC before completing all three reading passes
- Place file in wrong folder due to incomplete topic analysis
- Forget to update related MDCs
- Miss code examples embedded in text
- Skip mathematical formulas
- Ignore performance metrics
- Create duplicate content without cross-referencing

### DO:
- Read every word of the paper
- Extract complete code examples
- Preserve all technical details
- Document all assumptions
- Cross-reference related content
- Verify completeness multiple times
- Ask for clarification if paper is unclear
- Take time to understand complex sections

